0. Illinois has four distinct seasons: spring, summer, fall, and winter, with hot and humid summers, cold and snowy winters, and transitional seasons of spring and fall.

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Lisle, Illinois specificially:

0a. spring:

Spring in Lisle, Illinois, is a season of highly fluctuating temperatures and increasing precipitation, transitioning from cold, winter-like conditions in March to mild, almost summer-like weather by late May. 
Temperature
Temperatures increase significantly throughout the season: 
March: Daily highs average around 47°F (8°C) and lows around 31°F (-1°C). Winter weather, including snow, can still occur.
April: Conditions become moderately chilly, with average highs of about 59°F (15°C) and lows around 38°F (3°C). There can be significant temperature swings, with warm days followed by near-freezing nights.
May: The weather becomes much milder, with average highs of around 71°F (21°C) and lows around 52°F (11°C). The chance of muggy conditions also begins to increase toward the end of the month. 
Precipitation
Spring is typically the beginning of the wetter season in Lisle, with increasing rainfall from March through May. 
Rainfall increases rapidly, with May and June being the wettest months of the year.
Snowfall is still possible in March and early April but becomes very rare by May.
Sudden and heavy rain is common, making waterproof gear necessary. 
Other Conditions
Wind tends to be higher in April than in the summer months.
Cloud cover gradually decreases as the season progresses, leading to more clear or partly cloudy days by late May.
The area near Lake Michigan may experience slightly cooler temperatures and enhanced winter snowfall compared to areas further inland. 

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
0b. summer, 

Summer in Lisle, Illinois, is generally warm, long, and can be wet with moderate to high humidity. 
Temperature
Average Highs: Daily high temperatures range from the low to mid-80s F (around 81°F in June to a peak of 85°F in July). Highs rarely exceed 92°F.
Average Lows: Nighttime low temperatures are typically in the low to mid-60s F (around 62°F in June, rising to 66°F in July). Lows rarely fall below 50°F. 
Precipitation and Humidity
Rainfall: Summer is part of the wetter season in Lisle. June is typically the wettest month of the year, with an average of about 4.1 inches of rain. There is a chance of rain on many days throughout the summer months.
Humidity: The perceived humidity increases significantly during the summer, from "comfortable" to "muggy" or even "oppressive," especially in July and August. 
Sunshine and Wind
Sunshine: The summer months feature a good amount of sunshine, with August being the clearest month of the year, having clear, mostly clear, or partly cloudy conditions about 67% of the time.
Wind: Winds are generally calmer in the summer compared to other seasons, with average speeds around 8 mph. 
Overall, the weather is warm and suitable for outdoor activities from mid-June to mid-September. 

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
0c. fall, 

In Lisle, Illinois, fall weather is characterized by a rapid decrease in temperature and humidity, transitioning from mild, late-summer conditions in September to cold, early-winter conditions by late November. 
Temperature
Temperatures drop significantly throughout the season.
Month 	Average High (°F)	Average Low (°F)
September	~76°F (24°C)	~57-59°F (14-15°C)
October	~63°F (17°C)	~44-47°F (7-8°C)
November	~49°F (9°C)	~31-35°F (0-2°C)
September is the mildest, with temperatures that can still reach the 80s°F early in the month.
October sees a noticeable chill set in, with daytime highs becoming much cooler and overnight lows often falling into the upper 30s°F.
November is cold, with temperatures regularly near or below freezing, signaling the approach of winter. 
Precipitation and Snowfall
Rain is the primary form of precipitation, but the chance of snow increases significantly in November.
Rainfall is generally consistent across the fall months, with an average of around 2.25 to 3.5 inches per month.
The chance of a wet day decreases slightly as the season progresses, from about 31% in September to 23% by the end of November.
Snow is rare in September and October (trace amounts are possible), but average snowfall in November can accumulate to a couple of inches, with a chance of mixed rain and snow events occurring. 
Other Conditions
Cloud Cover: The season starts with relatively clear skies in September, but cloud cover increases rapidly through October and November, with mostly cloudy conditions becoming common by the end of the season.
Humidity: The air becomes much drier throughout the fall. The muggy conditions of summer quickly disappear, making for a more comfortable humidity level by October and November.
Growing Season: The first freeze of the season typically occurs around mid-October, marking the end of the growing season. 

============================================================================
0d. winter,

In Lisle, Illinois, winter weather is typically freezing, snowy, and windy, characterized by cold temperatures and significant snowfall. The cold season generally lasts from December to March. 
Key Characteristics
Temperatures: Winters are cold, with average daily high temperatures ranging from the low 30s to mid-30s°F and average lows in the teens to low 20s°F. January is typically the coldest month, with average lows around 16–17°F and highs around 31–32°F. Temperatures rarely fall below -3°F or rise above 55°F.
Snowfall: Lisle experiences a significant snowy period from around mid-November to the end of March. The area receives an annual snowfall of approximately 28 inches, with the most snow typically falling in January and February. The average snowfall for the northern Illinois area is slightly higher at 39.8 inches.
Precipitation: Precipitation often occurs as snow or a mix of rain and snow. The chance of a "wet day" (at least 0.04 inches of liquid-equivalent precipitation) is around 22% at the start of winter, decreasing slightly by the end of the season.
Wind and Cloud Cover: The winter months are often windy, with average wind speeds around 17-18 mph in January and December, which can make the cold feel even more severe (wind chill factor). The sky is also frequently overcast or mostly cloudy, especially in December.
Conditions: The combination of cold temperatures, wind, and snow means heavy winter clothing (e.g., thick winter coat and gloves) is necessary. 
In summary, expect a proper, cold winter with a good amount of snow and frequent cloud cover if you are in Lisle, Illinois.

